## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose of the SDD

This Software Design Document (SDD) translates the functional and non-functional requirements defined in the Vitalis Software Requirements Specification (SRS) into a concrete, implementable software design. Vitalis is a **business-to-consumer (B2C) cross-platform mobile application** that combines an **NLP-driven journaling chatbot**, a **metabolic trend dashboard**, an **educational hub**, and **curated wellness product recommendations** — designed with a strong focus on the **South Asian (Pakistani) lifestyle context**.

The intended audiences for this document are:

- **Mobile Engineers** — for client-side implementation in Flutter/React Native.
- **Backend Engineers** — for API, NLP-orchestration, and data-pipeline implementation.
- **QA Engineers** — for design-driven test planning.
- **DevOps Engineers** — for cloud infrastructure provisioning and monitoring.
- **Project Stakeholders & Academic Supervisors** — for traceability and acceptance.
- **Content & Operations Team** — to understand the admin portal and content workflow.

The document conforms to **IEEE Std 1016-2009**, extended pragmatically with modern concerns: NLP integration, cross-platform mobile architecture, cultural localization, and privacy-by-design for health data.

### 1.2 Scope of the System

**In-Scope (v1.0):**

- User account lifecycle (registration → email verification → login → profile → account deletion).
- NLP-driven conversational logging of **diet, mood, and symptoms** in plain English.
- Shortcut/structured commands (e.g., `/mood tired`, `/ate biryani`) for fast entry.
- Confidence-based confirmation flow with fallback re-prompting.
- Persistent, editable daily log timeline.
- Trend analytics dashboard with charts and PDF export.
- Simple correlation hints between habits and symptoms.
- Categorised educational hub with search, full-text articles, and bookmarking.
- Curated wellness product recommendations with external (affiliate) links.
- Web-based admin portal for content, product, and analytics management.

**Out-of-Scope (deferred):**

- Medical diagnosis or treatment recommendation.
- Integration with Electronic Health Records (EHR) or HL7/FHIR.
- Real-time vital-sign monitoring or wearable device sync.
- In-app purchase / payment processing.
- Roman-Urdu NLP (queued as a phase-2 enhancement).
- Telemedicine / live consultation with clinicians.

