### 2.3 Assumptions & Dependencies

**Assumptions:**

- Users have reliable 3G/4G/5G connectivity for chatbot interaction.
- The chosen NLP provider maintains its published 99.9% SLA.
- The user base in v1.0 is concentrated in Pakistan; latency to the nearest cloud region (e.g., `me-south-1` or `asia-south1`) is ≤150 ms.
- Users consent to health-data collection at first launch (explicit, granular consent screen).

**Dependencies:**

| Dependency | Type | Risk if Unavailable |
|---|---|---|
| Gemini API (default) / OpenAI API (fallback) | External SaaS | Chat degraded; manual & shortcut logging still work (NFR-13) |
| MongoDB Atlas (M10+ for v1.0) | Managed DB | Total outage |
| Firebase Auth (optional, alternative to in-house JWT) | Managed Auth | Login disabled |
| Redis (Upstash or ElastiCache) | Cache & rate-limit | Sessions/throttling degrade |
| SendGrid SMTP | Email | Verification & reset emails blocked |
| Cloud object storage (S3 / GCS / Firebase Storage) | Media | Article images broken |

### 2.4 Constraints

- **Technical:** Cross-platform mobile (Flutter chosen — see §4.5); backend in Node.js (chosen over Python Flask — see §4.5); NoSQL DB (MongoDB chosen — see §4.5).
- **Regulatory:** Pakistan PDP Bill (draft) and GDPR-equivalent principles applied for forward compatibility.
- **Budgetary:** Academic / early-stage budget. Free / low-tier managed services preferred; no dedicated SRE team.
- **Temporal:** Single-semester (~14–16 weeks) build window; small team (2–4 engineers).
- **Cultural:** UI copy and NLP examples must respect local food vocabulary and gender norms (PCOS-specific content sensitivities).

