## 4. Architectural Design

### 4.1 Chosen Architectural Style

After evaluating alternatives, the system adopts a **Layered (N-Tier) Architecture with a Modular Monolith backend**, accessed by a **cross-platform mobile client** and a **web-based admin portal**.

| Style | Suitability | Verdict |
|---|---|---|
| Microservices | Premature for 10K-MAU scale; ops cost too high | ❌ Rejected |
| Serverless (FaaS) | Cold starts conflict with NFR-01 (≤3s); long-lived NLP streams awkward | ⚠️ Used only for scheduled jobs (e.g., trend recompute) |
| **Modular Monolith (chosen)** | Clear module boundaries; horizontally scalable; small-team friendly | ✅ **Adopted** |
| Event-Driven / CQRS | No high-throughput event firehose justifies complexity | ❌ Rejected |

The monolith is internally partitioned into modules (Auth, Logging, NLP, Trends, Hub, Products, Admin) with well-defined service interfaces, enabling future extraction if scale demands.

