### 6.3 Physical Storage Considerations

- **Database:** MongoDB Atlas — minimum **M10 (replica set)** in v1.0; upgrade to **M30 with sharded cluster** when active users exceed ~50K.
- **Sharding Key (future):** `{ userId: 'hashed' }` — distributes load evenly while keeping each user's data co-located.
- **Field-Level Encryption (FLE):** `log_entries.symptom`, `users.healthGoals` encrypted with MongoDB Client-Side Field-Level Encryption (CSFLE) using a Customer Master Key in GCP KMS — protects PHI even from DB administrators.
- **Object Storage:** GCS bucket with object-level ACLs and signed URLs for PDF exports (5-min TTL).

### 6.4 Data Dictionary (Excerpt)

| Collection | Field | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| users | email | String | unique, lowercase | RFC 5322 validated |
| users | passwordHash | String(60) | not null | bcrypt cost 12 |
| users | healthGoals | String[] | enum-tagged | encrypted at field level |
| log_entries | type | enum | indexed | gates which sub-document is populated |
| log_entries | nlpConfidence | Number(0–1) | optional | null for shortcut/manual entries |
