## 8. Security & Privacy Design

### 8.1 Authentication & Authorization

**Authentication:** JWT with refresh-token rotation (NFR-07).

| Token | Algorithm | TTL | Client Storage | Server Storage |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Access Token | RS256 | 15 min | Secure Storage (iOS Keychain / Android Keystore) | None |
| Refresh Token | RS256 | 7 days | Secure Storage | Hashed `jti` in Redis |

**Refresh rotation** — each `/auth/refresh` issues a new refresh token and revokes the prior one. Detected reuse → entire chain revoked → forced re-login.

**Authorization:** **RBAC** with two roles (`user`, `admin`) enforced by Express middleware (NFR-09):

```javascript
const requireRole = (role) => (req, res, next) =>
  req.user?.role === role ? next() : res.status(403).json({ error: 'Forbidden' });

router.get('/admin/articles', authenticate, requireRole('admin'), AdminController.listArticles);
```

### 8.2 Data Encryption

| Data | At Rest | In Transit |
|---|---|---|
| User credentials | bcrypt cost 12 (NFR-06) | TLS 1.3 (NFR-05) |
| MongoDB | Atlas-managed AES-256 (NFR-08) | TLS 1.3 |
| Sensitive fields (symptoms, healthGoals) | **CSFLE** with GCP KMS Customer Master Key | TLS 1.3 |
| Object storage | GCS server-side encryption + signed URLs | HTTPS |
| Secrets (API keys, JWT private key) | GCP Secret Manager (KMS-encrypted) | TLS |
| Logs | Encrypted log group | TLS |
| Mobile local storage | iOS Keychain / Android EncryptedSharedPreferences | — |

### 8.3 Input Validation & Sanitization

Every endpoint declares a **Joi schema** validated by `validate(schema)` middleware. Mobile-side validation mirrored via `freezed` models — server is always the source of truth.

```javascript
const chatLogSchema = Joi.object({
  message: Joi.string().trim().min(1).max(1000).required()
});
```

Article rendering uses **DOMPurify**-sanitised Markdown → HTML; the mobile client renders via `flutter_markdown` with a strict allowlist.

### 8.4 OWASP Mobile Top 10 (2024) Mitigation

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| **M1 Improper Credential Usage** | Tokens only in Secure Storage; never in shared_prefs/UserDefaults |
| **M2 Inadequate Supply Chain** | `flutter pub outdated`, `npm audit`, Renovate Bot weekly |
| **M3 Insecure Authentication** | JWT + biometric step-up after 15-min idle |
| **M4 Insufficient Input/Output Validation** | Joi server-side + freezed client-side |
| **M5 Insecure Communication** | TLS 1.3, certificate pinning on mobile (Dio interceptor) |
| **M6 Inadequate Privacy Controls** | Explicit health-data consent; export & delete endpoints (FR-06) |
| **M7 Insufficient Binary Protections** | R8/ProGuard (Android) + bitcode (iOS); Flutter obfuscation `--obfuscate --split-debug-info` |
| **M8 Security Misconfiguration** | `helmet` on backend; secure defaults; CI policy-as-code |
| **M9 Insecure Data Storage** | CSFLE for PHI; local Hive boxes encrypted with key from Secure Storage |
| **M10 Insufficient Cryptography** | bcrypt 12, RS256 JWT, AES-256, TLS 1.3 |

### 8.5 Audit Logging (NFR-10)

The `audit_logs` collection captures privileged & sensitive events, retained **90 days** via TTL index:

| Action | Actor | Metadata |
|---|---|---|
| `USER_REGISTERED` | self | `{ ipHash }` |
| `LOGIN_SUCCESS` / `LOGIN_FAILURE` | self / — | `{ ipHash, ua }` |
| `ACCOUNT_DELETION_REQUESTED` | self | `{ reason? }` |
| `ADMIN_ARTICLE_PUBLISHED` | admin | `{ articleId }` |
| `NLP_PROVIDER_FALLBACK` | system | `{ from, to, errorCode }` |

Logs are append-only from the app (no `update`/`delete` exposed) and shipped to Cloud Logging for tamper resistance.

### 8.6 Privacy & Compliance

- **Consent Management:** Granular consent screen at first launch (health-data, marketing). Revocable at any time in Profile → Privacy.
- **Right to Access:** `GET /me/export` returns a JSON archive of all user data within 30 days.
- **Right to Erasure (FR-06):** Soft delete → 30-day grace → hard purge. Anonymized analytics may be retained (hash-only `userId`).
- **Data Minimization:** Age, sex, goals optional; raw chat text not sent to NLP if shortcut path matches.
- **Disclosure:** Privacy policy explicitly lists Gemini/OpenAI as sub-processors and the categories of data shared (only the user's most recent message; no PII attached).
- **Children:** Service restricted to users **≥13** (declared at signup); under-13 accounts rejected.

