## 9. Performance & Scalability Design

### 9.1 Expected Load & Capacity Planning

| Metric | v1.0 Target | Growth (v2.0) |
|---|---|---|
| Concurrent users | 10,000 (NFR-03) | 50,000 |
| Requests/sec | 100 (NFR-04) | 500 |
| Daily log entries | ~80,000 | ~500,000 |
| Storage growth | ~50 MB/day | ~300 MB/day |
| NLP calls/month (est.) | ~1.5M | ~9M |

### 9.2 Caching Strategy

| Cache Layer | Tool | TTL | Invalidation |
|---|---|---|---|
| CDN (Cloudflare) | Edge | Static assets 1y, API responses bypass | Versioned filenames |
| Mobile in-app | Hive + Dio cache interceptor | Articles 24h; trends 5 min | Manual on edit |
| Redis: NLP utterance cache | Redis | 1 h | Auto-expire |
| Redis: dashboard rollup pointer | Redis | 5 min | Worker write |
| Redis: rate-limit counters | Redis | 60s window | Auto-expire |
| Redis: session/JWT-jti revocation | Redis | until token expiry | On logout |
| MongoDB Atlas | WiredTiger | LRU | — |

### 9.3 Database Optimization

**Indexes (defined in §6.2):**

| Index | Supports |
|---|---|
| `users.email` (unique) | Login lookup |
| `log_entries.{userId, timestamp:-1}` | Timeline (FR-13) |
| `log_entries.{userId, type, timestamp:-1}` | Trend aggregations (FR-14) |
| `articles` text index `{title:10, tags:5, body:1}` | Search (FR-20) |
| `bookmarks.{userId, articleId}` unique | Bookmark uniqueness |
| `audit_logs.createdAt` TTL 90d | NFR-10 |

**Query Budget:** Every endpoint completes its DB work within **≤150 ms p95**; slow queries (>300 ms) auto-logged. Aggregations on `log_entries` use the indexed prefix `{userId, timestamp}` to avoid full collection scans.

**Connection Pooling:** Mongoose pool (`maxPoolSize: 25`) per Node instance; exhaustion alerts at >85%.

### 9.4 Horizontal vs. Vertical Scaling

- **App Tier (stateless):** Horizontal — Cloud Run scales by request concurrency (target 80 req/instance).
- **MongoDB:** Vertical first (M10 → M30 → M50), then shard on `userId`.
- **Redis:** Vertical until v2.0; consider Redis Cluster afterward.
- **NLP:** Provider abstraction permits **multi-provider load-balancing** when one provider rate-limits.

### 9.5 Load Balancing & CDN

- **L7 Load Balancer** with least-outstanding-requests algorithm — superior to round-robin for variable-latency NLP calls.
- **CDN:** Cloudflare for `/cdn/articles/*` images and admin web bundle; Brotli compression enabled.
- **Mobile Asset Bundling:** App shell precaches critical fonts/icons; article images lazy-loaded with `cached_network_image`.

