## 10. Error Handling & Logging

### 10.1 Exception Handling Strategy

Three-tier taxonomy:

```typescript
// Tier 1: Domain errors (expected; 4xx)
class ValidationError extends DomainError { status = 400; }
class AuthenticationError extends DomainError { status = 401; }
class AuthorizationError extends DomainError { status = 403; }
class NotFoundError extends DomainError { status = 404; }
class RateLimitError extends DomainError { status = 429; }

// Tier 2: Integration errors (5xx + retry hints)
class NLPUnavailableError extends IntegrationError { status = 503; }
class NLPTimeoutError extends IntegrationError { status = 504; }

// Tier 3: Programmer errors (500 + alert)
class UnexpectedError extends Error { status = 500; }
```

A central Express error middleware logs full context, sanitizes responses (no stack traces in prod), and emits RFC-7807 problem details. **Unhandled rejections** kill the process; the orchestrator restarts — avoiding zombie state.

**Graceful Degradation (NFR-13):**

- NLP outage → rule-based extractor + banner *"AI helper temporarily limited — shortcut commands still work."*
- Email service outage → registration succeeds; verification email queued for retry.
- Object storage outage → PDF export queued; user notified when ready.

### 10.2 Logging Framework & Levels

- **Library:** Pino (JSON), one event per line, redacted before serialization.
- **Correlation:** `requestId` (UUID) per request, propagated to NLP via `X-Request-ID`.
- **PII Hygiene:** Redactor strips `password`, `token`, `authorization`, `rawText`, `email` from logs (mobile and backend).

| Level | Use |
|---|---|
| `fatal` | Process-killing error |
| `error` | Request failed unexpectedly |
| `warn` | Recoverable issues (retry succeeded, fallback engaged) |
| `info` | Request boundaries, lifecycle |
| `debug` | Per-request diagnostics (dev only) |

### 10.3 Monitoring & Alerting

| Signal | Tool | Threshold | Action |
|---|---|---|---|
| HTTP 5xx rate | Prometheus / Cloud Monitoring | >2% over 5 min | Page on-call |
| `/logs/chat` p95 | Prometheus | >3s for 10 min (NFR-01) | Warning |
| NLP error rate | Prometheus | >10% over 5 min | Auto-switch provider |
| Mongo connection saturation | Prometheus | >85% | Auto-scale signal |
| NLP cost (token spend) | Custom metric | >120% of daily budget | Notify product owner |
| Login failure rate | Loki | >50/min from single IP | Auto-block 1h |
| Crash-free sessions (mobile) | Sentry / Crashlytics | <99.5% | Hotfix |

A **Grafana dashboard** consolidates: request rate, error rate, NLP confidence histogram, cost, MAU/DAU, crash-free rate.

